%N_PENDULUM_DRIVER - A code to simulate an N-pendulum.%%   Uses Lagrange's equations to solver for the equations of motion and%   a numerical ODE solver to integrate the free response from random%   initial conditions.%%   Other m-files required: EquationDerivation.m%   See Also: EQUATIONDERIVATION.m%%   Author: Noel Csomay-Shanklin%   Email Address: noelcs@gatech.edu%   Last Revision: 19-Feb-2018
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Set Up<a name="2"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

clear;clc;clear ODE_N_Pend
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Get number of segments from user<a name="3"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

n = 5;
% while (n&lt;3 || n &gt; 10)%     prompt = ('Please enter the number of segments:\n\n');% %     n = input(prompt);%     if n &lt; 3%         fprintf('The simulation does not work with fewer than 3 segments.\n')%     end%     if n &gt; 10%         fprintf(['Because everything is being solved symbolically, any\n'...%             'values above 10 will make it take too long to execute.\n'])%     end% end
EquationDerivation(n); % Derive Equations of Motion
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Define characteristics of pendulum<a name="4"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

m = ones(1,n); % Mass [kg]
I = ones(1,n)*1/3; % Inertia [kg m^2]
l = ones(1,n); % Length [m]
d = ones(1,n)*0.5; % Distance to COM [m]
g = 10; % Gravity [m s^-2]
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Define characteristics of animation<a name="5"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

framepersec = 50;
T = 10;
tspan = linspace(0,T,T*framepersec);
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Define Initial Conditions and ODE Options<a name="6"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

z0 = [];
for i = 1:1:n
    theta(i) = rand(1)*pi;
    thetad(i) = rand(1);
    z0 = [z0 theta(i) thetad(i)];
end
options=odeset('abstol',1e-9,'reltol',1e-9);
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>ODE<a name="7"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

[t z] = ode45('ODE_N_Pend',tspan,z0,options, m, I, l, d, g);
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Animate Results<a name="8"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

figure('units','normalized','outerposition',[0 0 1 1])
subplot(1,2,1)
hold onfor i = 1:n
    plot(t, z(:,i));
end
anim = subplot(1,2,2);
for i=1:length(tspan)
if ~ishghandle(anim)
        close all        break    end
    pause(1/framepersec)
    xm = 0;
    ym = 0;
for j = 2:1:n+1
        xm(j)=xm(j-1)+l(j-1)*sin(z(i,1+2*(j-2)));
        ym(j)=ym(j-1)-l(j-1)*cos(z(i,1+2*(j-2)));
        plot([0],[0],'ko','MarkerSize',5); %pivot point    end
    hold on    for k = 1:1:n
        plot([xm(k) xm(k+1)],[ym(k) ym(k+1)],'r','LineWidth',2);% first pendulum    end

    axis([-sum(l) sum(l) -sum(l) sum(l)]);
    axis square
    hold offend
{% endhighlight %}
